<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12127&amp;p=137534#p137534"><![CDATA[
I'm guessing if you look inside it, you're not going to see much other than a cartridge connector and an blob of epoxy.  Unless you see something obviously wrong, broken wires or something, it's probably not going to be fixable.  It's really be faster to just return it.  If you can open it without breaking a warranty, it won't hurt to look inside but I doubt it would help.<br /><br />I don't have any of the newer clones, but with Retro Bit I can say I bought their NES controller extension cables to compare to 2 other manufacturers, and the Retro Bit cables were by far the shittiest, with unbelievably small wire gauge.  I would avoid their stuff, if the build quality is this bad.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Fri Dec 12, 2014 10:19 pm</p><hr />
