1. The company that makes it is named <a href="http://hyperkin.com/retron-1-nes-gaming-system-black.html" class="postlink">Hyperkin</a> (they also make a white-and-red version).  <a href="http://hyperkin.com/contact-us" class="postlink">Contact them</a> for support; this forum has no relation to Hyperkin or their products (you're free to discuss them here, but this is not where you get support for Hyperkin products).<br /><br />2. I don't think it matters where you bought it, though if you bought it used that may be a problem.  Furthermore, Hyperkin sells stuff directly on Amazon.<br /><br />3. If you still don't like the product, <strong>send it back to Amazon!</strong>  They can exchange it with another one free of charge (you pay no shipping fees), otherwise just send it back and get your money refunded.  If the replacement has the same issue, they'll refund your money as well.  It's that simple.  Amazon is one of the few companies left in the United States who is <strong>extremely</strong> good about refunding a customer's money.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3">koitsu</a> — Fri Dec 12, 2014 6:19 pm</p><hr />
